  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Executive / Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support the sales team in driving sales of our public speaking  curriculum package through proactive prospecting, lead generation, and  nurturing client relationships.</li>\n  <li>Assist in conducting thorough needs assessments to understand prospective clients' requirements and help tailor solutions to meet their specific needs.</li>\n  <li>Aid in delivering compelling sales presentations and demonstrations to showcase the value proposition of our curriculum package.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with the sales manager to meet and exceed sales targets and key performance indicators (KPIs) on a consistent basis.</li>\n  <li>Follow up with clients to ensure attendance at trial classes and provide additional support as needed.</li>\n  <li>Generate leads during down time.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>A proven track record of success in sales, preferably in the education or curriculum sales industry.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of the sales process, from prospecting to closing deals.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, negotiation, and presentation skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a collaborative team.</li>\n  <li>Thrives in a sales-driven environment.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in English and other languages, with excellent communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to commit on both weekends.</li>\n  <li>Fresh Graduates are welcome</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Pay: <strong>$4,000.00 - $6,000.00 per month</strong></p>\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Additional leave</li>\n  <li>Flexible schedule</li>\n  <li>Health insurance</li>\n  <li>Parental leave</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Schedule:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>5-Day work week (Inclusive of Weekends)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Supplemental Pay:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Commission pay</li>\n  <li>Performance bonus</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Sales: 1 year (Preferred)</li>\n</ul>",
